{
  "texts": [
    "Originally introduced by Vaswani et al.",
    "in 2017 [1], Transformers have achieved great notoriety for their state-of-the-art performance across most language modeling tasks.",
    "Despite this success, their internal mechanisms remain difficult to understand, motivating extensive work in mechanistic interpretability (see Section 1).",
    "Since our experiments focus on analyzing decoder-only Transformers (e.g., GPT-2 [2] and LLaMa [3]), we begin by providing a brief overview of the Transformer architecture.",
    "To ensure clarity amongst various terminologies in recent literature, we also establish a consistent set of terms that will be used throughout this paper."
  ]
}